title: J.F. Kiely Construction Co. Participates in 17th Annual Community Day Event for the Borough of Tinton Falls
text:
J.F. Kiely Construction Co.
LONG BRANCH, N.J. , Oct. 5, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- J.F. Kiely Construction Co., a leading utility construction company headquartered in Long Branch, New Jersey , proudly supports the Borough of Tinton Falls' 17 th Annual Community Day event by providing several pieces of its construction equipment for public display as part of the Borough's Touch-A-Truck feature.
"Supporting our communities through wonderful events like this is an easy decision for us," said John M. Kiely , President of J.F. Kiely Construction Co. "My father and I have always believed that we should invest in and support the communities in which we serve," Kiely continued.
About the Tinton Falls Borough Community Day Event:
The Borough of Tinton Falls will be hosting its 17th Annual Community Day on Sunday, October 11 . The Borough's goal is to bring the residents of their community together for a day of fun in conjunction with community awareness. We rely on the merchants in our area to assist in providing entertainment or highlight your products and services.
This event is well attended by community members of all ages in which they find it to be enjoyable as well as informative.
The Touch-A-Truck feature is a fun, family event enjoyed by children of all ages! This event features an assortment of different kinds of vehicles from police cars, fire trucks, bull dozers, cranes, tanks, classic cars and even a helicopter! Children are encouraged to sit behind the steering wheels, take pictures and explore everything about their favorite vehicles. There will be no entry fees, however donations to the Borough are accepted. This year's event is Sunday, October 11, 2015 from 3 p.m. until 7 p.m. at the Sycamore Recreation Complex.
About J.F. Kiely Construction Co.:
J.F. Kiely Construction Co. is a turnkey provider of underground utility infrastructure including gas, water, sewer and electric. Established in 1952, J.F. Kiely Construction Co. performs work for public utility companies, municipalities and private contractors. J.F. Kiely Construction Co. employs hundreds of professionals and union employees in multiple locations throughout New Jersey and Pennsylvania .
For more information about J.F. Kiely Construction Co. please visit http://www.JFKIELY.com or contact James M. Pagano at (732) 222-4400.
